ology’s centrality and importance in any analysis of the global human predicament. Thinking beyond the State will find wide application in anthropology, political science and philosophy courses dealing with the state and globalization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aGlobalizationxSocial aspects. 0aInternational economic integrationxPolitical aspects. 0aInternational economic relationsxPolitical aspects. 0aNation-state and globalization. 4aAnthropology. 4aPhilosophy. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aanthropology, political philosophy, globalization, global human predicament, contemporary social scientists.1 aHaince, Marie-Claude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarcus, George E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRousseau, Phillip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170936440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501709364423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501709364/original  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles